{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:psalms.47",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 47,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 47 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:1",
      "text": "A psalm of a canticle, for the sons of Core, on the second day of the week.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:2",
      "text": "Great is the Lord, and exceedingly to be praised in the city of our God, in his holy mountain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:3",
      "text": "With the joy of the whole earth is mount Sion founded, on the sides of the north, the city of the great king.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:4",
      "text": "In her houses shall God be known, when he shall protect her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:5",
      "text": "For behold the kings of the earth assembled themselves: they gathered together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:6",
      "text": "So they saw, and they wondered, they were troubled, they were moved:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:7",
      "text": "Trembling took hold of them. There were pains as of a woman in labour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:8",
      "text": "With a vehement wind thou shalt break in pieces the ships of Tharsis.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:9",
      "text": "As we have heard, so have we seen, in the city of the Lord of hosts, in the city of our God: God hath founded it for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:10",
      "text": "We have received thy mercy, O God, in the midst of thy temple.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:11",
      "text": "According to thy name, O God, so also is thy praise unto the ends of the earth: thy right hand is full of justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:12",
      "text": "Let mount Sion rejoice, and the daughters of Juda be glad; because of thy judgments, O Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:13",
      "text": "Surround Sion, and encompass her: tell ye in her towers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:14",
      "text": "Set your hearts on her strength; and distribute her houses, that ye may relate it in another generation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.47.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 47,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 47:15",
      "text": "For this is God, our God unto eternity, and for ever and ever: he shall rule us for evermore.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
